1
00:01:08,300 --> 00:01:10,800
"Blue Lips"

2
00:01:11,200 --> 00:01:13,700
(Episode 6)

3
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:20,000
Is it good?

4
00:01:22,900 --> 00:01:23,900
I didn't expect

5
00:01:24,500 --> 00:01:25,500
you to know how to cook.

6
00:01:25,760 --> 00:01:26,480
I'm single, you know.

7
00:01:26,679 --> 00:01:27,679
Just the basics.

8
00:01:41,239 --> 00:01:42,279
Why are you looking at me?

9
00:01:45,719 --> 00:01:46,719
Nothing.

10
00:01:46,840 --> 00:01:47,840
I just think

11
00:01:47,920 --> 00:01:49,840
you look really especially
good without makeup.

12
00:01:52,179 --> 00:01:53,819
It's not like you haven't seen it before.

13
00:01:55,900 --> 00:01:57,440
I did see it last time,

14
00:01:57,679 --> 00:01:59,399
but you're wearing different clothes today.

15
00:01:59,960 --> 00:02:01,160
It gives off a different vibe.

16
00:02:01,400 --> 00:02:02,880
You look more like a college student.

17
00:02:09,519 --> 00:02:10,639
Can I ask you a question?

18
00:02:14,039 --> 00:02:15,380
Besides working at Blue Moon,

19
00:02:15,539 --> 00:02:17,099
do you have any other part-time jobs?

20
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:21,120
I don't mean anything by it.

21
00:02:21,480 --> 00:02:22,860
I just feel like

22
00:02:22,980 --> 00:02:24,135
I've seen you somewhere before.

23
00:02:24,159 --> 00:02:25,159
You look really familiar.

24
00:02:28,219 --> 00:02:28,760
Why

25
00:02:29,119 --> 00:02:30,119
are you asking this?

26
00:02:31,619 --> 00:02:32,619
Just curious.

27
00:02:35,880 --> 00:02:36,880
I

28
00:02:37,280 --> 00:02:38,760
also deliver packages during the day.

29
00:02:39,539 --> 00:02:40,539
Why?

30
00:02:43,039 --> 00:02:43,480
Nothing.

31
00:02:43,880 --> 00:02:45,019
I just find it strange.

32
00:02:46,099 --> 00:02:46,840
Looking at your place,

33
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:49,300
you don't seem to be doing too badly.

34
00:02:50,280 --> 00:02:51,840
Why are you working day and night?

35
00:02:52,400 --> 00:02:53,720
Are you that desperate for money?

36
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:57,659
Well, you smoke and play games every day.

37
00:02:57,960 --> 00:02:59,179
Your fridge is always empty.

38
00:02:59,380 --> 00:03:00,420
Food, daily necessities...

39
00:03:00,460 --> 00:03:01,700
You don't care about any of it.

40
00:03:02,300 --> 00:03:03,580
Don't you find your life boring?

41
00:03:05,480 --> 00:03:06,480
Okay, okay.

42
00:03:07,039 --> 00:03:07,659
Pretend I didn't ask.

43
00:03:08,039 --> 00:03:09,599
You don't owe me an explanation anyway.

44
00:03:10,019 --> 00:03:11,019
Eat up.

45
00:03:20,659 --> 00:03:21,659
Wait.

46
00:03:23,840 --> 00:03:24,840
Weren't you

47
00:03:25,139 --> 00:03:26,139
going home?

48
00:03:26,639 --> 00:03:27,639
You should hurry back.

49
00:03:31,739 --> 00:03:32,739
The last bus

50
00:03:32,800 --> 00:03:34,079
is already gone.

51
00:03:39,340 --> 00:03:42,000
Besides, I was the one who
offered to treat you to a meal.

52
00:03:42,940 --> 00:03:43,940
Let me clean this up.

53
00:03:48,320 --> 00:03:49,320
Then,

54
00:03:51,099 --> 00:03:52,739
maybe I should take a shower too.

55
00:04:22,599 --> 00:04:23,760
Do you want to dry your hair?

56
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:26,200
You'll catch a cold otherwise.

57
00:05:12,539 --> 00:05:13,539
Don't stop.

58
00:05:15,079 --> 00:05:16,079
Why did you stop playing?

59
00:05:18,860 --> 00:05:19,860
Want to request a song?

60
00:05:23,119 --> 00:05:24,679
Is there a charge for requests tonight?

61
00:05:28,199 --> 00:05:29,480
No extra charge.

62
00:05:32,960 --> 00:05:33,960
Then I'll request.

63
00:05:34,800 --> 00:05:35,940
"Dawn, Please Don't Come."

64
00:05:37,539 --> 00:05:38,539
Such an old song.

65
00:05:39,500 --> 00:05:41,060
Aren't you worried I might not know it?

66
00:05:42,519 --> 00:05:43,519
I'm sure you do.

67
00:05:49,739 --> 00:05:54,099
Dawn, I beg you,

68
00:05:54,480 --> 00:05:57,619
please don't come.

69
00:05:59,260 --> 00:06:03,079
Let the illusion of tonight

70
00:06:03,659 --> 00:06:06,639
last forever.

71
00:06:41,960 --> 00:06:43,000
You saw everything.

72
00:06:43,300 --> 00:06:44,440
Why didn't you save me?

73
00:06:48,079 --> 00:06:49,519
With the situation I'm in right now,

74
00:06:49,960 --> 00:06:51,860
what right do I have to
drag someone else down?

75
00:06:54,860 --> 00:06:55,860
Alright.

76
00:06:55,980 --> 00:06:57,239
Get some rest if you're tired.

77
00:06:58,119 --> 00:06:59,119
I'm going to sleep.

78
00:07:59,500 --> 00:08:00,780
You're up so early.

79
00:08:02,679 --> 00:08:03,780
I have to go to work.

80
00:08:06,699 --> 00:08:08,739
Let me make you some breakfast.

81
00:08:13,019 --> 00:08:14,099
Don't bother.

82
00:08:15,039 --> 00:08:16,039
No way.

83
00:08:16,699 --> 00:08:18,419
Skipping breakfast is bad for your stomach.

84
00:08:18,619 --> 00:08:19,020
Listen to me.

85
00:08:19,640 --> 00:08:20,260
Go

86
00:08:20,420 --> 00:08:21,860
wash your face and brush your teeth.

87
00:08:22,100 --> 00:08:23,595
There are new toothbrushes in the cabinet.

88
00:08:23,619 --> 00:08:24,720
Grab one for yourself.

89
00:08:25,500 --> 00:08:26,500
Go on.

90
00:08:54,079 --> 00:08:55,079
Time to eat.

91
00:08:57,380 --> 00:08:58,380
We're out of milk.

92
00:08:58,520 --> 00:08:59,899
Just make do with some hot water.

93
00:09:03,899 --> 00:09:04,976
Why is there only one portion?

94
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:06,000
Aren't you eating?

95
00:09:06,380 --> 00:09:07,980
I'm going back to sleep after you leave.

96
00:09:08,420 --> 00:09:09,420
I'm exhausted.

97
00:09:12,979 --> 00:09:15,500
Did I wake you up?

98
00:09:16,619 --> 00:09:17,635
What are you talking about?

99
00:09:17,659 --> 00:09:18,659
Hurry up and eat.

100
00:09:36,340 --> 00:09:37,340
Brother Mo!

101
00:09:37,420 --> 00:09:39,060
What a coincidence running into you here.

102
00:09:39,520 --> 00:09:40,819
You actually cook for yourself?

103
00:09:45,420 --> 00:09:46,420
Are you seeing someone?

104
00:09:49,166 --> 00:09:50,185
What are you talking about??

105
00:09:50,479 --> 00:09:52,359
If I were dating, would
I still go to your bar?

106
00:09:52,960 --> 00:09:55,436
You know what, you could
totally find someone at our bar.

107
00:09:55,460 --> 00:09:56,079
Someone like me?

108
00:09:56,080 --> 00:09:57,318
The girls at our bar
are pretty good-looking.

109
00:09:57,319 --> 00:09:58,439
How am I fit to date anyone?

110
00:10:00,220 --> 00:10:00,960
People from the bar...

111
00:10:01,140 --> 00:10:03,020
Can you just bring someone from a bar home?

112
00:10:04,439 --> 00:10:05,699
That's a harsh thing to say.

113
00:10:06,220 --> 00:10:06,619
So,

114
00:10:07,079 --> 00:10:08,079
are you coming tonight?

115
00:10:08,619 --> 00:10:09,619
We'll see tonight.

116
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:10,500
Enjoy your shopping.

117
00:10:10,720 --> 00:10:11,100
I'm off.

118
00:10:11,680 --> 00:10:12,439
Take care, Brother Mo!

119
00:10:12,479 --> 00:10:13,479
Bye!

120
00:10:25,319 --> 00:10:26,319
Brother Heng.

121
00:10:26,899 --> 00:10:27,899
No song requests today?

122
00:10:28,819 --> 00:10:29,819
Hold on, let me check.

123
00:10:38,039 --> 00:10:39,039
Nope.

124
00:10:41,279 --> 00:10:44,260
It's a bit less fun without
Brother Mo around.

125
00:10:46,100 --> 00:10:47,100
Is he not coming today?

126
00:10:48,720 --> 00:10:50,180
When I saw him earlier today,

127
00:10:50,819 --> 00:10:51,959
he said he had to look after his shop,

128
00:10:51,960 --> 00:10:52,960
so he wouldn't make it.

129
00:10:55,039 --> 00:10:56,079
But I think

130
00:10:56,420 --> 00:10:58,380
it's definitely not that simple.

131
00:11:01,020 --> 00:11:02,020
Why?

132
00:11:03,460 --> 00:11:04,460
Why else?

133
00:11:04,859 --> 00:11:06,460
A bachelor suddenly stops partying?

134
00:11:07,500 --> 00:11:09,380
He must have someone
waiting for him at home.

135
00:11:10,779 --> 00:11:11,779
Do you

136
00:11:11,880 --> 00:11:13,060
know who it is?

137
00:11:14,359 --> 00:11:15,359
No idea.

138
00:11:15,779 --> 00:11:16,560
I even asked him

139
00:11:16,699 --> 00:11:18,720
if he found someone at our place.

140
00:11:19,319 --> 00:11:20,659
He said no matter what,

141
00:11:20,899 --> 00:11:22,919
he would never bring
someone he met at a bar

142
00:11:22,920 --> 00:11:24,100
back to his home.

143
00:11:26,079 --> 00:11:26,760
Do you think he

144
00:11:26,761 --> 00:11:28,119
looks down on us bar workers?

145
00:11:29,720 --> 00:11:31,140
He's always fooling around,

146
00:11:31,300 --> 00:11:32,840
it's not like he's anything special.

147
00:11:34,159 --> 00:11:35,180
Running a shop like that.

148
00:11:52,619 --> 00:11:53,619
A box of Vandacon.

149
00:11:56,819 --> 00:11:58,819
Why don't you have an
umbrella in this heavy rain?

150
00:12:00,100 --> 00:12:01,100
What's wrong with you?

151
00:12:01,680 --> 00:12:03,000
What does it have to do with you?

152
00:12:07,760 --> 00:12:09,280
Are you planning to go back like this?

153
00:12:10,220 --> 00:12:11,300
Let me get you an umbrella.

154
00:12:11,680 --> 00:12:12,680
Let go.

155
00:12:14,619 --> 00:12:15,619
Look at you,

156
00:12:15,739 --> 00:12:16,739
your hands are freezing.

157
00:12:19,699 --> 00:12:20,699
Let go!

158
00:12:21,140 --> 00:12:21,500
Listen to me.

159
00:12:22,079 --> 00:12:23,276
Go upstairs and take a hot shower,

160
00:12:23,300 --> 00:12:24,300
or you'll catch a cold.

161
00:12:26,300 --> 00:12:27,300
Stop messing around.

162
00:12:31,220 --> 00:12:32,340
I'm not going to your place.

163
00:12:32,779 --> 00:12:33,939
Didn't you think I was dirty?

164
00:12:34,392 --> 00:12:35,952
Aren't you afraid I'll dirty your home?

165
00:12:36,100 --> 00:12:37,100
Who said you were dirty?

166
00:12:37,300 --> 00:12:38,420
If anyone is dirty, it's me.

167
00:12:38,779 --> 00:12:40,100
I run a sex toy shop.

168
00:12:42,659 --> 00:12:44,060
Then why didn't you come today?

169
00:12:45,760 --> 00:12:47,060
Should I tell the truth?

170
00:12:49,380 --> 00:12:50,380
On rainy days,

171
00:12:50,600 --> 00:12:51,818
my rheumatism acts up and my knees hurt.

172
00:12:51,819 --> 00:12:52,819
I didn't want to go out.

173
00:12:54,880 --> 00:12:55,880
Just because of that?

174
00:12:57,239 --> 00:12:58,239
What else?

175
00:13:06,899 --> 00:13:07,899
Why wouldn't I go?

176
00:13:08,920 --> 00:13:09,920
I want to go home.

177
00:13:09,960 --> 00:13:11,795
If you go back like this
and really catch a cold,

178
00:13:11,819 --> 00:13:13,219
how are you going to work tomorrow?

179
00:13:15,520 --> 00:13:16,520
I'd be better off dead.

180
00:13:18,100 --> 00:13:19,540
What nonsense are you talking about?

181
00:13:22,739 --> 00:13:23,739
Listen to me.

182
00:13:24,800 --> 00:13:26,120
Don't act tough with your health.

183
00:13:37,760 --> 00:13:39,616
You should drink ginger
tea when you have a cold.

184
00:13:39,640 --> 00:13:40,640
I just brewed it for you.

185
00:13:41,039 --> 00:13:41,359
Here.

186
00:13:41,600 --> 00:13:42,600
Try it.

187
00:13:43,100 --> 00:13:44,100
Let me wipe it for you.

188
00:13:50,720 --> 00:13:51,720
Is it spicy?

189
00:13:52,859 --> 00:13:53,859
No.

190
00:13:53,939 --> 00:13:54,939
It's sweet.

191
00:13:55,100 --> 00:13:56,319
I added brown sugar.

192
00:13:57,500 --> 00:13:58,060
Drink it all up.

193
00:13:58,260 --> 00:13:59,860
You won't catch a cold if you finish it.

194
00:14:05,239 --> 00:14:06,799
Why didn't you bring your guitar today?

195
00:14:08,420 --> 00:14:09,420
Because

196
00:14:09,680 --> 00:14:10,680
I left it at the bar.

197
00:14:11,140 --> 00:14:11,859
I didn't have an umbrella,

198
00:14:12,159 --> 00:14:13,519
and I was afraid it would get wet.

199
00:14:15,840 --> 00:14:17,619
You're afraid a guitar might get wet,

200
00:14:18,060 --> 00:14:19,780
but aren't you more precious than a guitar?

201
00:14:22,420 --> 00:14:23,700
No matter how good something is,

202
00:14:24,159 --> 00:14:25,375
it still needs someone to cherish it

203
00:14:25,399 --> 00:14:26,399
to show its true value.

204
00:14:28,659 --> 00:14:29,960
If no one cares about it,

205
00:14:31,119 --> 00:14:32,159
even a diamond

206
00:14:33,140 --> 00:14:34,760
will be seen as just a rock.

207
00:14:36,819 --> 00:14:37,819
Silly.

208
00:14:38,060 --> 00:14:39,060
People are people.

209
00:14:39,380 --> 00:14:40,380
Not diamonds,

210
00:14:40,680 --> 00:14:41,680
not rocks.

211
00:14:42,399 --> 00:14:43,538
Don't let whether others cherish you or not

212
00:14:43,539 --> 00:14:44,819
make you think less of yourself.

213
00:14:50,500 --> 00:14:51,500
Much better.

214
00:14:52,579 --> 00:14:53,579
Then drink it all.

215
00:14:53,800 --> 00:14:54,880
I'm going to take a shower.

216
00:14:55,020 --> 00:14:56,239
Go to bed early.

217
00:15:13,100 --> 00:15:14,100
What are you looking at?

218
00:15:14,779 --> 00:15:15,779
The rain stopped.

219
00:15:16,840 --> 00:15:18,720
I'm checking if there
are any stars in the sky.

220
00:15:21,220 --> 00:15:21,859
It's cloudy.

221
00:15:22,079 --> 00:15:23,359
Where would the stars come from?

222
00:15:28,979 --> 00:15:30,399
Can I call you Shixian from now on?

223
00:15:33,199 --> 00:15:34,199
Sure.

224
00:15:36,239 --> 00:15:37,239
Shixian.

225
00:15:38,899 --> 00:15:39,899
How old are you?

226
00:15:41,060 --> 00:15:42,060
Twenty-one.

227
00:15:42,920 --> 00:15:43,920
And you?

228
00:15:45,359 --> 00:15:46,359
Thirty.

229
00:15:47,939 --> 00:15:48,939
At thirty,

230
00:15:50,359 --> 00:15:51,399
I've accomplished nothing.

231
00:15:54,500 --> 00:15:55,920
But I think you're pretty great.

232
00:15:58,159 --> 00:16:00,319
Just like what you said
when we first argued,

233
00:16:01,279 --> 00:16:02,619
ending up like me

234
00:16:03,260 --> 00:16:04,399
really isn't that great.

235
00:16:06,859 --> 00:16:07,859
I was just...

236
00:16:08,079 --> 00:16:09,079
I know.

237
00:16:10,260 --> 00:16:10,800
That was...

238
00:16:11,199 --> 00:16:12,479
You were just bickering with me.

239
00:16:13,220 --> 00:16:14,260
I didn't take it to heart.

240
00:16:19,180 --> 00:16:20,180
Shixian.

241
00:16:21,779 --> 00:16:22,779
From now on,

242
00:16:22,979 --> 00:16:24,339
can you stop working at Blue Moon?

243
00:16:24,800 --> 00:16:25,800
Find a proper job.

244
00:16:26,399 --> 00:16:27,696
When you're tired, come to my place.

245
00:16:27,720 --> 00:16:28,340
Have a meal,

246
00:16:28,579 --> 00:16:29,600
and get some good rest.

247
00:16:31,079 --> 00:16:32,520
I'll leave a spare key for you.

248
00:16:38,319 --> 00:16:39,460
I have my own difficulties.

249
00:16:43,520 --> 00:16:44,520
For money?

250
00:16:47,779 --> 00:16:48,779
You could say that.

251
00:16:49,840 --> 00:16:51,040
Why don't you just be with me?

252
00:16:56,859 --> 00:16:57,859
You want to keep me?

253
00:16:58,859 --> 00:16:59,859
No, I...

254
00:17:00,180 --> 00:17:01,180
That's not what I meant.

255
00:17:01,619 --> 00:17:02,619
I...

256
00:17:03,680 --> 00:17:05,040
I don't know what's wrong with me.

257
00:17:09,800 --> 00:17:10,800
Lately,

258
00:17:11,119 --> 00:17:12,759
why haven't you been coming to Blue Moon?

259
00:17:15,079 --> 00:17:16,159
Didn't I promise you?

260
00:17:17,680 --> 00:17:18,760
If you drank that medicine,

261
00:17:19,159 --> 00:17:21,519
I wouldn't request songs that
disgust you for a few months.

262
00:17:27,380 --> 00:17:28,399
Is he not coming today?

263
00:17:28,899 --> 00:17:30,380
He said no matter what,

264
00:17:30,600 --> 00:17:32,559
he can't bring someone he met at a bar

265
00:17:32,560 --> 00:17:33,680
back to his home.

266
00:17:34,180 --> 00:17:34,779
Do you think he

267
00:17:34,780 --> 00:17:36,180
looks down on us bar workers?

268
00:17:39,260 --> 00:17:39,979
I don't know how...

269
00:17:39,979 --> 00:17:40,979
I understand.

270
00:17:41,319 --> 00:17:42,479
If I don't agree,

271
00:17:44,079 --> 00:17:45,000
will you just

272
00:17:45,001 --> 00:17:46,439
disappear without a word again?

273
00:17:50,560 --> 00:17:51,760
Pretend I didn't say anything.

274
00:17:52,640 --> 00:17:53,859
It's not like we're dating.

275
00:18:07,520 --> 00:18:08,659
Then get your money ready.

276
00:18:25,020 --> 00:18:26,140
In your potato rice...?

277
00:18:26,739 --> 00:18:28,259
It's actually just pan-fried potatoes.

278
00:18:29,859 --> 00:18:30,859
You're done.

279
00:18:33,760 --> 00:18:34,159
Then,

280
00:18:34,479 --> 00:18:36,399
you've turned down all the clients, right?

281
00:18:43,880 --> 00:18:44,880
You two.

282
00:18:46,100 --> 00:18:47,100
Ah Heng.

283
00:18:47,640 --> 00:18:48,640
Lately,

284
00:18:48,779 --> 00:18:50,140
that new cocktail you mixed

285
00:18:50,359 --> 00:18:51,439
doesn't taste very good.

286
00:18:53,020 --> 00:18:54,020
I don't think so.

287
00:18:54,899 --> 00:18:56,299
Anyway, it's not selling very well.

288
00:18:57,319 --> 00:18:58,319
Do you know why?

289
00:19:02,079 --> 00:19:03,520
You should change the salt rim

290
00:19:03,819 --> 00:19:05,119
to a sugar rim.

291
00:19:08,840 --> 00:19:09,840
Why?

292
00:19:09,899 --> 00:19:10,899
Because you are

293
00:19:11,680 --> 00:19:14,366
too salty. [pun for: you have too much free
time [to be messing around in my business.]]

294
00:19:16,720 --> 00:19:18,039
I'm too salty?

295
00:19:21,619 --> 00:19:23,339
You're the one who's too salty, Brother Mo.

296
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:28,000
Have a taste.

297
00:19:30,020 --> 00:19:31,439
Who taught you how to cook?

298
00:19:32,060 --> 00:19:33,060
Do I even need to learn?

299
00:19:33,300 --> 00:19:34,980
I just watched a video and figured it out.

300
00:19:35,840 --> 00:19:37,375
When I first came to Jinyang,
I wasn't used to the food,

301
00:19:37,399 --> 00:19:39,079
so I learned to make some Fengzhou dishes.

302
00:19:39,159 --> 00:19:40,159
Just to make do.

303
00:19:42,079 --> 00:19:43,199
You're from Fengzhou?

304
00:19:46,800 --> 00:19:48,140
Then why did you come to Jinyang?

305
00:19:52,720 --> 00:19:53,920
That was years ago.

306
00:19:54,020 --> 00:19:55,020
I forgot.

307
00:19:55,859 --> 00:19:56,859
Eat.

308
00:20:02,819 --> 00:20:03,819
It's delicious.

309
00:20:14,079 --> 00:20:15,079
So?

310
00:20:15,180 --> 00:20:16,439
Is the cat I gave you pretty?

311
00:20:17,300 --> 00:20:18,720
I picked it out very carefully.

312
00:20:19,319 --> 00:20:20,319
Do you like it?

313
00:20:20,800 --> 00:20:21,800
I like it.

314
00:20:22,880 --> 00:20:23,880
Don't you feel

315
00:20:23,979 --> 00:20:25,000
they're a perfect match?

316
00:20:25,800 --> 00:20:26,800
A perfect match.

317
00:20:26,859 --> 00:20:27,859
It looks like you.

318
00:20:28,760 --> 00:20:29,760
Then that one is you.

319
00:20:32,359 --> 00:20:33,359
I think

320
00:20:34,119 --> 00:20:35,279
compared to before,

321
00:20:36,159 --> 00:20:37,659
you're a little different.

322
00:20:40,840 --> 00:20:41,840
Yeah.

323
00:20:42,039 --> 00:20:43,039
I've gotten older.

324
00:20:45,020 --> 00:20:46,340
You used to

325
00:20:46,899 --> 00:20:48,300
seem more like a decent guy.

326
00:20:50,760 --> 00:20:52,579
Are you saying I'm not decent now?

327
00:20:53,739 --> 00:20:54,739
Now,

328
00:20:55,500 --> 00:20:56,699
you're like a sly old fox.

329
00:20:57,260 --> 00:20:58,976
Who are you calling
an old fox? Who's a fox?

330
00:20:59,000 --> 00:20:59,699
Who's an old fox?

331
00:20:59,800 --> 00:21:00,119
Wait.

332
00:21:00,760 --> 00:21:01,760
I have something for you.

333
00:21:03,600 --> 00:21:04,600
What is it?

334
00:21:05,479 --> 00:21:06,479
Close your eyes.

335
00:21:07,560 --> 00:21:09,000
You're not going to hit me, are you?

336
00:21:10,020 --> 00:21:10,520
Do you want it or not?

337
00:21:10,960 --> 00:21:11,960
Yes, yes, yes.

338
00:21:22,220 --> 00:21:23,220
Alright.

339
00:21:25,800 --> 00:21:26,800
For me?

340
00:21:27,319 --> 00:21:28,699
It's not some prank toy, is it?

341
00:21:29,359 --> 00:21:30,359
Open it and see.

342
00:21:33,479 --> 00:21:34,479
How is it?

343
00:21:36,579 --> 00:21:37,579
It looks great.

344
00:21:42,000 --> 00:21:43,240
It's not a holiday or anything,

345
00:21:43,420 --> 00:21:44,580
why are you giving me a gift?

346
00:21:45,220 --> 00:21:46,460
I saw it when I was passing by,

347
00:21:46,899 --> 00:21:48,460
thought it suited you, so I bought it.

348
00:21:50,039 --> 00:21:51,300
Then when you bought it,

349
00:21:52,340 --> 00:21:53,340
what were you thinking?

350
00:21:54,859 --> 00:21:55,859
I thought

351
00:21:56,460 --> 00:21:58,199
you look better in a suit,

352
00:21:58,399 --> 00:21:59,399
so I bought it for you.

353
00:22:01,460 --> 00:22:03,239
You just like me in a suit?

354
00:22:03,680 --> 00:22:04,100
Yeah.

355
00:22:04,101 --> 00:22:05,381
Then do you like me as a person?

356
00:22:06,720 --> 00:22:07,800
I give you a gift,

357
00:22:08,239 --> 00:22:09,479
and you have so many questions.

358
00:22:09,760 --> 00:22:11,200
I'm never giving you anything again.

359
00:22:12,920 --> 00:22:14,080
You have to keep buying them.

360
00:22:14,579 --> 00:22:15,579
You gave it to me,

361
00:22:15,640 --> 00:22:16,640
so it's mine.

362
00:22:18,880 --> 00:22:19,180
Come here.

363
00:22:19,380 --> 00:22:20,380
Put it on me.

364
00:22:21,239 --> 00:22:22,239
Tie it for me.

365
00:22:22,760 --> 00:22:23,140
I...

366
00:22:23,260 --> 00:22:24,340
I don't know how to tie it.

367
00:22:27,000 --> 00:22:28,000
I'll teach you.

